Why GPL-3.0-or-later
--------------------
This software loads KiCad's `pcbnew` Python module in-process (for PCB
geometry, connectivity and via analysis). `pcbnew` is part of KiCad and is
licensed under GPL-3.0; combining with it in-process makes this a derivative
work, so the project as a whole is distributed under GPL-3.0-or-later.

The IPC paths (`kipy`) and `kicad-cli` invocations are arm's-length (separate
process) and do not themselves impose the GPL, but the in-process `pcbnew`
usage does, and it governs the combined work.


